.TH "sysfs_ctlreg_read" 9 "sysfs_ctlreg_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sysfs_ctlreg_read \- Read method for reading from ctlreg
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" sysfs_ctlreg_read
.BI "(struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "struct kobject *kobj "  ","
.BI "struct bin_attribute *bin_attr "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ","
.BI "loff_t off "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "filp" 12
open sysfs file
.IP "kobj" 12
kernel kobject that contains the kernel class device.
.IP "bin_attr" 12
kernel attributes passed to us.
.IP "buf" 12
if successful contains the data from the adapter IOREG space.
.IP "off" 12
offset into buffer to beginning of data.
.IP "count" 12
bytes to transfer.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Accessed via /sys/class/scsi_host/hostxxx/ctlreg.
Uses the adapter io control registers to read data into buf.
.SH "RETURN"
-ERANGE off and count combo out of range
-EINVAL off, count or buff address invalid
value of count, buf contents read
